I will elaborate on the analogy.<br>
<br>
burger king:taco bell::daoc:everquest<br>
mcdonalds:taco bell::anarchyonline:everquest<br>
jackinthebox:taco bell::ultimaonline:everquest<br>
fastfoodstore4:taco bell::mmorpg4:everquest<br>
<br>
and so on...<br>
<br>
The food chains offer very similar products, marketed at similar consumers and are in extremely close competition with each other.<br>
<br>
The same goes for the mmorpg world, with one exception: everquest has no competition.<br>
<br>
Supply is extremely low, demand has flooded probably beyond what SOE could have predicted.  Couple that with how people are already immersed into everquest and are therefor much less likely to even consider a competitors product.<br>
<br>
What happens?  Well...just be lucky that SOE only raised it three bucks (keep in mind thats 30% already).  Im sure they would retain a significant amount of subscribers even if they raised their prices two fold in one hike.<br>
