  I'm married, have an almost 4 year old, have had my salary impacted by the economy and the attack, may move to another city in the next two years, but I probably won't get thrown into prison. I have more money in uncashed checks lying around than 2 years of EQ costs. I'm talking about uncashed for over a year. If I want to risk wasting money by buying a 2 year subscription to a service I may not use, the amount isn't very much to me. To other people it makes sense to stick to month to month. I used to go from game to game when I got new games every week, usually for free. Between family and EQ, I've hardly played a dozen in the last year.<br>
<br>
  Actually, I'm trying to decide whether to cancel, or just buy the 2 year lease. It's not the money that's a bother, it's the time I spend in EQ that's my major consideration. The price increase just prompts a general reevaluation of EQ as entertainment. Also, if I die, what do I care about the loss? I guess if I go blind or lose my arms that subscription would be annoying. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujeminiikricket.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeminii Kricket</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/29/02 6:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3211.topic&index=51>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ subscritions going up 30%???</span><hr size=1> my version of the patch msg....<br>
